Tender Almond Cake
  --AI (possibly appropriated from Salvatore Messina)

8 oz (227 g)blanched almonds, ground into coarse meal
6 large eggs, separated
1 1/4 c (250 g) sugar
zest of 1 orange and 1 lemon
1/4 tsp almond extract
confectioners' sugar (for dusting)

Preheat oven to 350F/175C; grease a 9" springform pan, lining the bottom with parchment. Beat yolks and sugar until pale, then mix in almonds, zests, and extract. In another bowl, beat egg whites to stiff peaks, then gently fold into the almond mixture. Pour into prepared pan and bake for 40-50 min, until a toothpick inserted into the middle comes out clean. Cool completely and dust with confectioners' sugar (if desired)

